leigh Medal and Prize|publisher=Institute of Physics|accessdate=3 October 2014}}</ref> He obtained his PhD from the University of Newcastle upon Tyne in 1985, with a thesis entitled \"Quantum aspects of Kaluza-Klein cosmologies\"<ref>{{Cite thesis|title=Quantum aspects of Kaluza-Klein cosmologies|url=https://ethos.bl.uk/OrderDetails.do?uin=uk.bl.ethos.355071|publisher=University of Newcastle upon Tyne|date=1985|degree=Ph.D.|first=E. J.|last=Copeland}}</ref>.\n\nCopeland is well known for his appearances on the physics-popularizing [[YouTube]] channel [[Brady Haran|Sixty Symbols]], as well as the mathematics-popularizing channel [[Numberphile]].\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Copeland, Edmund}}\n[[Category:Academics of the University of Nottingham]]\n[[Category:Mathematics popularizers]]\n[[Category:Science communicators]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n\n\n{{UK-physicist-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Professor of physics}}\n{{Infobox scientist\n| name          = Edmund Copeland\n| honorific_suffix = \n| image         = \n| alt           = \n| caption       = \n| birth_name    = Edmund Copeland\n| birth_date    = \n| birth_place   = \n| death_date    = \n| death_place   = \n| residence     = United Kingdom\n| nationality   = British\n| fields        =\n  {{plainlist |\n* [[Particle physics in cosmology|Particle Cosmology]]\n  }}\n| workplaces    =\n  {{plainlist |\n* [[University of Sussex]]\n* [[University of Nottingham]]\n  }}\n| alma_mater    = [[University of Newcastle upon Tyne|Newcastle University]]\n| doctoral_advisor = [[Paul Davies]]\n| thesis_title  = \n| thesis_url    = 1985\n| thesis_year   = \n| academic_advisors = \n| doctoral_students = \n| known_for     =\n  {{plainlist |\n* [[Science outreach]]\n* [[Sixty Symbols]]\n  }}\n| awards        =\n  {{plainlist  |\n* [[Royal Society Wolfson Research Merit Award|Wolfson Research Merit Award]]\n* [[Raylei